[thinking] **Analyzing project setup**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering the evidence: POM has no dependencies, and the core jar is self-contained. Normal usage only requires filesystem, temp directories, or RAMDirectory, without needing a service. The build issues are more about code incompatibility than setup.
[thinking] 
[thinking] I see that the existing build.gradle includes --add-opens, but it’s part of the current scaffold, not a new advisory preparation. If tests avoid MMapDirectory or use RAMDirectory, I wonder if this setup could change with new support.
